    "body": "Hi\r\n\r\nyes, your´e right. Copying with the commandline also changes the attribute.\r\n\r\nHowever - I don´t understand the sense!\r\nA copied file should be an 100% copy. That he creation date is changed is understandable, but changing of attributes....\r\n\r\nIMHO is he archive-attribute a marker for backup/archiving. If every copied/moved file haves this attribute it would mean that every file will be backed up - or I have double work to remove the attribute.\r\n\r\nWell - if its so I have to live with it. \r\nBut IMHO it doesn't make any sense.",
